    <item>
      <title>Research Month: If AI Can Write the Essay, What Are We Teaching? at Founders Library </title>
      <description><![CDATA[<div>  <img src="https://localist-images.azureedge.net/photos/52551230861182/huge/e92d975e016e9dd548e847a1e80df680785897e0.jpg" style="width: 100%;" />  <div style="font-size: 0.9em; color: #555;"><strong>Mon, 20 Apr 2026</strong></div>  <div><p>Generative AI is reshaping how students learn, how faculty teach, and how knowledge is assessed. As AI tools can now produce essays and analyses with ease, higher education faces a critical question: If AI can write the essay, what are we teaching?</p>

<p> </p>

<p>3:30 – 4:00 p.m. | Networking Reception</p>

<p>4:00 – 5:00 p.m. | Program</p>

<p> </p>

<p>In-Person Location: Founders Browsing Room 101, Founders Library</p>

<p>Online via Zoom: <a href="https://howard.zoom.us/webinar/register/WN_0T6RxA35T3CxCg6CSybKGg">https://howard.zoom.us/webinar/register/WN_0T6RxA35T3CxCg6CSybKGg</a></p>

<p> </p>

<p>Join us in person or online for this hybrid session to explore how educators can respond—rethinking assignments, redefining rigor, and designing learning experiences that emphasize critical thinking, originality, and meaningful engagement. Drawing on work from the Cornell Center for Teaching Innovation, the conversation will highlight both the challenges and opportunities AI presents across disciplines.</p>

<p> </p>

<p>The program will feature a presentation by Dr. Rob Vanderlan, Associate Director of the Center for Teaching Innovation at Cornell University, followed by a fireside conversation moderated by Dr. Kyndra V. Middleton, Professor and Interim Director of the Center for Excellence in Teaching, Learning, and Assessment (CETLA) at Howard University, and audience Q&amp;A.</p>

<p> </p>

<p>Faculty, staff, students, and partners are encouraged to attend and engage in this timely conversation about the future of teaching and learning.</p>

<p> </p>

<p>This session is free and open to the Howard University community and the public.</p>

<p><a href="https://events.howard.edu/event/research-month-if-ai-can-write-the-essay-what-are-we-teaching">View on site</a> | <a href="mailto:?subject=I found an interesting event%3A Research Month%3A If AI Can Write the Essay%2C What Are We Teaching%3F&amp;body=I found an interesting event you may like%3A%0A%0A%0ADate%3A Apr 20%2C 2026%0A%0ADescription%3A%0AGenerative AI is reshaping how students learn%2C how faculty teach%2C and how knowledge is assessed. As AI tools can now produce essays and analyses with ease%2C higher education faces a critical question%3A If AI can write the essay%2C what are we teaching%3F%0A%0A %0A%0A3%3A30 %E2%80%93 4%3A00 p.m. %7C Networking Reception%0A%0A4%3A00 %E2%80%93 5%3A00 p.m. %7C Program%0A%0A %0A%0AIn-Person Location%3A Founders Browsing Room 101%2C Founders Library%0A%0AOnline via Zoom%3A https%3A%2F%2Fhoward.zoom.us%2Fwebinar%2Fregister%2FWN_0T6RxA35T3CxCg6CSybKGg%0A%0A %0A%0AJoin us in person or online for this hybrid session to explore how educators can respond%E2%80%94rethinking assignments%2C redefining rigor%2C and designing learning experiences that emphasize critical thinking%2C originality%2C and meaningful engagement. Drawing on work from the Cornell Center for Teaching Innovation%2C the conversation will highlight both the challenges and opportunities AI presents across disciplines.%0A%0A %0A%0AThe program will feature a presentation by Dr. Rob Vanderlan%2C Associate Director of the Center for Teaching Innovation at Cornell University%2C followed by a fireside conversation moderated by Dr. Kyndra V. Middleton%2C Professor and Interim Director of the Center for Excellence in Teaching%2C Learning%2C and Assessment %28CETLA%29 at Howard University%2C and audience Q%26A.%0A%0A %0A%0AFaculty%2C staff%2C students%2C and partners are encouraged to attend and engage in this timely conversation about the future of teaching and learning.%0A%0A %0A%0AThis session is free and open to the Howard University community and the public.%0A%0Ahttps%3A%2F%2Fevents.howard.edu%2Fevent%2Fresearch-month-if-ai-can-write-the-essay-what-are-we-teaching%0A">Email this event</a></p></div></div>]]></description>
